00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.152 position:50% align:center
I didn't.

00:10:11.236 --> 00:10:13.238 position:50% align:center
It's back in the
student council office.

00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:14.406 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Same.

00:10:14.489 --> 00:10:16.825 position:50% align:center
A warehouse that's
almost never used, and.

00:10:16.908 --> 00:10:19.577 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] No way to call for
assistance.

00:10:19.661 --> 00:10:21.955 position:50% align:center
[yells] So what do you
think we should do?!

00:10:22.038 --> 00:10:24.541 position:50% align:center
Nothing! We're
done for! [grunts]

00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:27.502 position:50% align:center
Without food or water,
we're goners for sure! Dammit!

00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:32.340 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA crying]
Oh, no!

00:10:32.424 --> 00:10:33.758 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Yeah, right!

00:10:33.842 --> 00:10:36.928 position:50% align:center
This is straight out of the
Shinomiya playbook.

00:10:37.012 --> 00:10:39.723 position:50% align:center
Something like this would
never happen in real life.

00:10:39.806 --> 00:10:42.559 position:50% align:center
And those fake tears
aren't fooling anyone.

00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:46.646 position:50% align:center
She's clearly employing
the suspension bridge effect.

00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:50.233 position:50% align:center
I'm onto your game, but I'll
play along and act all nervous.

00:10:50.316 --> 00:10:52.444 position:50% align:center
Man, you've gotta be kidding me!

00:10:52.527 --> 00:10:54.487 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA continues crying]

00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:55.905 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA giggles]

00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:58.491 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] How utterly
adorable you are, President.

00:10:58.575 --> 00:11:01.619 position:50% align:center
Although, I think you made
your ploy a little too obvious.

00:11:01.703 --> 00:11:03.121 position:50% align:center
The chances of the door locking

00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:05.540 position:50% align:center
right after we talked
about it are slim to none.

00:11:05.623 --> 00:11:07.083 position:50% align:center
You're losing your touch.

00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:10.045 position:50% align:center
But it's quite unusual
for you to be so assertive.

00:11:10.128 --> 00:11:13.048 position:50% align:center
Especially if you're using
the tactic I think you are.

00:11:13.131 --> 00:11:15.008 position:50% align:center
You're trying to move
our relationship along

00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:17.469 position:50% align:center
by implementing the
suspension bridge effect.

00:11:17.552 --> 00:11:20.847 position:50% align:center
A pretty shallow way to go about
it, though, if I'm being honest.

00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:22.640 position:50% align:center
You clearly put some
thought into this though,

00:11:22.724 --> 00:11:25.060 position:50% align:center
so I'll do you a favor
and play along for now!

00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:27.395 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA gasps]
This is getting really scary!

00:11:27.479 --> 00:11:28.688 position:50% align:center
Ah! Damn!

00:11:28.772 --> 00:11:31.775 position:50% align:center
How are we gonna make
it out of this one?

00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:35.904 position:50% align:center
Open sesame!

00:11:35.987 --> 00:11:38.323 position:50% align:center
Is anyone out there?

00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:39.366 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
They're both pretending

00:11:39.449 --> 00:11:40.825 position:50% align:center
they're in serious trouble.

00:11:40.909 --> 00:11:43.661 position:50% align:center
But they actually are
in serious trouble.

00:11:43.745 --> 00:11:46.664 position:50% align:center
Since he thinks she set this up
and she thinks he set this up,

00:11:46.748 --> 00:11:49.167 position:50% align:center
the gravity of the
situation hasn't sunk in.

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:50.627 position:50% align:center
They're too busy
fantasizing about

00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:53.505 position:50% align:center
what might happen
next to be concerned!

00:11:57.884 --> 00:11:59.386 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA giggles]

00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:03.264 position:50% align:center
Oh, dear.

00:12:03.348 --> 00:12:06.518 position:50% align:center
What if no one
comes to rescue us?

00:12:06.601 --> 00:12:08.144 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:12:10.397 --> 00:12:12.565 position:50% align:center
It'll be fine. I'm here.

00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:14.567 position:50% align:center
President...

00:12:16.778 --> 00:12:18.446 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Taking advantage
of our predicament

00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:20.073 position:50% align:center
by grabbing my sleeve.

00:12:20.156 --> 00:12:21.908 position:50% align:center
And the Oscar goes to...!

00:12:21.991 --> 00:12:24.119 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
You touched me! You touched me!

00:12:24.202 --> 00:12:26.037 position:50% align:center
I can only imagine how
slick you must think you are

00:12:26.121 --> 00:12:27.580 position:50% align:center
for pulling off
such a cool move!

00:12:27.664 --> 00:12:28.623 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI, KAGUYA giggling]

00:12:28.707 --> 00:12:31.126 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Several hours later...

00:12:31.209 --> 00:12:32.252 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
I'm surprised by how long

00:12:32.335 --> 00:12:33.878 position:50% align:center
he's dragging this charade out.

00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:36.631 position:50% align:center
I guess that means he's
prepared for the long haul.

00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:38.341 position:50% align:center
But does that also mean...

00:12:38.425 --> 00:12:42.012 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I suspect what
she's ultimately after...

00:12:42.095 --> 00:12:44.305 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
...he wants to do this?

00:12:44.389 --> 00:12:46.725 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
...is something like that!

00:12:46.808 --> 00:12:48.852 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] It's a despicable
plan to pressure a girl

00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:50.937 position:50% align:center
in a psychologically
weakened state!

00:12:51.021 --> 00:12:54.107 position:50% align:center
One I will not be falling for!

00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:55.275 position:50% align:center
But...

00:12:55.358 --> 00:12:56.484 position:50% align:center
...well...

00:12:56.568 --> 00:12:58.319 position:50% align:center
Just to be sure,
I'll stick it out

00:12:58.403 --> 00:13:00.613 position:50% align:center
and see what the endgame
of his grand scheme is.

00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:02.365 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Although
neither of them is at fault

00:13:02.449 --> 00:13:03.867 position:50% align:center
for scheming anything,

00:13:03.950 --> 00:13:06.244 position:50% align:center
each is convinced that the
other has finally gathered up

00:13:06.327 --> 00:13:07.662 position:50% align:center
the courage to make a move,

00:13:07.746 --> 00:13:10.957 position:50% align:center
and the anticipation
is killing them!

00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:13.752 position:50% align:center
Something's bound
to happen! I can feel it!

00:13:13.835 --> 00:13:16.046 position:50% align:center
It's gotta be nighttime by now.

00:13:16.129 --> 00:13:18.965 position:50% align:center
I'm starting to
feel a bit chilly.

00:13:19.049 --> 00:13:22.594 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Whoa. She's more
brazen than I thought she was!

00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:25.430 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Shinomiya.

00:13:26.723 --> 00:13:27.474 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA gasps]

00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:28.808 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
That was fast!

00:13:28.892 --> 00:13:31.061 position:50% align:center
Shouldn't there be
more of a lead-in?

00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:33.688 position:50% align:center
So this is what
you were after, eh?

00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:35.815 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] He's actually
going for the kill!

00:13:35.899 --> 00:13:36.983 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Or is it something else?

00:13:37.067 --> 00:13:38.902 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
This is out of my comfort zone!

00:13:38.985 --> 00:13:40.236 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I don't
think I'm ready for that!

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:41.863 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA gasps]

00:13:44.074 --> 00:13:45.367 position:50% align:center
Shinomiya!

00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:47.535 position:50% align:center
[thud]

00:13:50.663 --> 00:13:53.667 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] 
'm scared.

00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:56.294 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Fairy tale
kisses happen in real life

00:13:56.378 --> 00:13:58.004 position:50% align:center
more often than people think.

00:13:58.088 --> 00:14:01.216 position:50% align:center
Kaguya discovered this for
herself in that moment.

00:14:01.299 --> 00:14:04.052 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
I'm scared, but...

00:14:04.135 --> 00:14:08.640 position:50% align:center
...I wonder what would happen
if I closed my eyes right now.

00:14:11.476 --> 00:14:12.977 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA grunts]

00:14:17.399 --> 00:14:19.693 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:25.699 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI gasps]

00:14:25.782 --> 00:14:28.243 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Fairy tale
kisses happen in real life

00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:30.537 position:50% align:center
more often than people think.

00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:33.748 position:50% align:center
Shirogane discovered this
for himself in that moment.

00:14:33.832 --> 00:14:36.418 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:14:40.964 --> 00:14:47.345 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Jeez. How long does
it take to check equipment?

00:14:47.429 --> 00:14:49.014 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA whimpers]

00:14:49.097 --> 00:14:49.848 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:14:49.931 --> 00:14:52.809 position:50% align:center
Thank you! So, so much!

00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:53.977 position:50% align:center
I was terrified!

00:14:54.060 --> 00:14:56.021 position:50% align:center
I'm so glad you found me!

00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:57.522 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA crying]

00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:59.190 position:50% align:center
You scumbag!

00:14:59.274 --> 00:15:02.986 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I can't say it was a
misunderstanding again!

00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:04.446 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Results for today's battle:

00:15:04.529 --> 00:15:07.949 position:50% align:center
They both lose, but just barely.

00:15:08.033 --> 00:15:09.534 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
This got stuck in the door?

00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:13.913 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Kill me now.
Everything about this sucks!

00:15:23.298 --> 00:15:24.966 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Take a look at this, Kaguya!

00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:27.635 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
What is it?

00:15:27.719 --> 00:15:28.678 position:50% align:center
Shinomiya.

00:15:28.762 --> 00:15:29.721 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:15:29.804 --> 00:15:31.806 position:50% align:center
You've got something
in your hair.

00:15:31.890 --> 00:15:36.561 position:50% align:center
Uh, what? Where?

00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:38.229 position:50% align:center
Allow me.

00:15:43.401 --> 00:15:45.612 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Oh, so I did.

00:15:45.695 --> 00:15:48.740 position:50% align:center
Pretty absentminded
of me not to notice, huh?

00:15:48.823 --> 00:15:52.327 position:50% align:center
Recently, I've kind of been...

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:53.870 position:50% align:center
...feeling...

00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:55.205 position:50% align:center
--[thud]
--[KAGUYA gasps]

00:15:56.206 --> 00:15:57.457 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:15:57.540 --> 00:15:58.917 position:50% align:center
Shinomiya!

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:00.585 position:50% align:center
My chest--it hurts.

00:16:00.669 --> 00:16:02.253 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Someone call for an ambulance!

00:16:02.337 --> 00:16:03.296 position:50% align:center
[YU] Already on it!

00:16:03.380 --> 00:16:04.214 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Get the school nurse, Iino!

00:16:04.297 --> 00:16:06.174 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Oh! Right!

00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:13.848 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
You know, Kaguya has never

00:16:13.932 --> 00:16:17.143 position:50% align:center
had a very strong
constitution to begin with.

00:16:17.227 --> 00:16:19.270 position:50% align:center
She gets sick every
time the seasons change

00:16:19.354 --> 00:16:21.481 position:50% align:center
and has to take
time off from school.

00:16:21.564 --> 00:16:25.360 position:50% align:center
If I'm not mistaken, her mother
passed away from heart disease.

00:16:25.443 --> 00:16:27.112 position:50% align:center
I never knew.

00:16:36.287 --> 00:16:37.706 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 8A]
Your attention, please.

00:16:37.789 --> 00:16:40.417 position:50% align:center
Doctor Tanuma is
making his rounds.

00:16:43.336 --> 00:16:44.963 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Shozo Tanuma.

00:16:45.046 --> 00:16:47.674 position:50% align:center
Considered to be one of
the world's top ten doctors,

00:16:47.757 --> 00:16:50.468 position:50% align:center
he's a master cardiologist
and the leading expert on

00:16:50.552 --> 00:16:53.513 position:50% align:center
pediatric cardiac
bypass surgery.

00:16:53.596 --> 00:16:54.681 position:50% align:center
His patients include

00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:57.267 position:50% align:center
some of the most
important people in Japan,

00:16:57.350 --> 00:17:00.687 position:50% align:center
such as the prime minister and
members of the Shinomiya family.

00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:02.272 position:50% align:center
Doctor.

00:17:04.107 --> 00:17:06.818 position:50% align:center
What? Did you say
the Shinomiya girl?

00:17:08.153 --> 00:17:09.612 position:50% align:center
I'm on my way.

00:17:09.696 --> 00:17:12.407 position:50% align:center
But, sir, you were asked to
attend the governor's party.

00:17:12.490 --> 00:17:14.617 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA]
They can wait.

00:17:14.701 --> 00:17:15.994 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
In that moment,

00:17:16.077 --> 00:17:19.873 position:50% align:center
Shozo Tanuma recalls
a vivid memory from the past.

00:17:21.583 --> 00:17:24.586 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] She was a girl who
didn't look forward to anything,

00:17:24.669 --> 00:17:28.048 position:50% align:center
with eyes as red as fire,
yet cold as ice.

00:17:28.131 --> 00:17:30.508 position:50% align:center
Apparently...

00:17:30.592 --> 00:17:33.219 position:50% align:center
...what goes around
comes around.

00:17:36.681 --> 00:17:39.809 position:50% align:center
If I had to guess,
I'd say it's arrhythmia.

00:17:39.893 --> 00:17:42.520 position:50% align:center
My heart started beating
fast out of nowhere.

00:17:42.604 --> 00:17:45.190 position:50% align:center
Then, I felt a pain in
my chest that was so bad,

00:17:45.273 --> 00:17:47.400 position:50% align:center
I thought I was going to die.

00:17:47.484 --> 00:17:50.945 position:50% align:center
Does that sound like
any disease you know of?

00:17:51.029 --> 00:17:52.447 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:17:52.530 --> 00:17:53.656 position:50% align:center
Going by what you've told me,

00:17:53.740 --> 00:17:57.118 position:50% align:center
I have a pretty good
idea of what it is.

00:17:57.202 --> 00:17:58.745 position:50% align:center
Please don't panic.

00:17:58.828 --> 00:18:01.664 position:50% align:center
Just listen to
what I have to say.

00:18:01.748 --> 00:18:03.708 position:50% align:center
All right.

00:18:03.792 --> 00:18:07.420 position:50% align:center
You are what's
known as "lovesick."

00:18:07.504 --> 00:18:09.047 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Uh...

00:18:10.590 --> 00:18:13.760 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Um, is that a
trendy name for some kind of

00:18:13.843 --> 00:18:15.345 position:50% align:center
heart disease I'm unaware of?

00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:16.846 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA]
No, what I'm referring to

00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:19.182 position:50% align:center
is the emotion you feel
when you're in love.

00:18:19.265 --> 00:18:22.227 position:50% align:center
Good one, Doctor. You really had
me going there for a minute.

00:18:22.310 --> 00:18:24.104 position:50% align:center
I'm not joking with you, though.

00:18:24.187 --> 00:18:26.064 position:50% align:center
So what you're saying is
I collapsed and was taken

00:18:26.147 --> 00:18:28.983 position:50% align:center
to a hospital in an ambulance
all because I'm in love?!

00:18:29.067 --> 00:18:31.194 position:50% align:center
Yes. I was a bit
disturbed as well at first

00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:32.821 position:50% align:center
because this is unprecedented.

00:18:32.904 --> 00:18:34.572 position:50% align:center
That's just utterly ridiculous!

00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:36.533 position:50% align:center
Someone else may well be in
love with me, but you can

00:18:36.616 --> 00:18:39.411 position:50% align:center
rest assured that I'd never
do anything so idiotic!

00:18:39.494 --> 00:18:41.454 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] She's a bit of a
firecracker, am I right?

00:18:41.538 --> 00:18:44.499 position:50% align:center
The kids call it
" <i>tsundere</i> ," sir.

00:18:44.582 --> 00:18:47.252 position:50% align:center
Is my personality
a disease, too?!

00:18:47.335 --> 00:18:49.379 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] Let's review
your symptoms, shall we?

00:18:49.462 --> 00:18:52.007 position:50% align:center
Earlier you told me that
your heart starts beating fast

00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:53.258 position:50% align:center
when you think
of certain someone

00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:54.509 position:50% align:center
during school activities.

00:18:54.592 --> 00:18:55.885 position:50% align:center
Yes. That's correct!

00:18:55.969 --> 00:18:57.679 position:50% align:center
é\And today,
that same certain someone

00:18:57.762 --> 00:18:59.806 position:50% align:center
removed a piece of
lint from your hair.

00:18:59.889 --> 00:19:02.058 position:50% align:center
When his hand brushed
your cheek ever so slightly,

00:19:02.142 --> 00:19:04.853 position:50% align:center
you began experiencing a
pulsating pain in your chest,

00:19:04.936 --> 00:19:06.688 position:50% align:center
not to mention
shortness of breath.

00:19:06.771 --> 00:19:09.190 position:50% align:center
Why are you repeating
what I just told you?!

00:19:10.692 --> 00:19:12.485 position:50% align:center
I'm afraid...

00:19:12.569 --> 00:19:13.403 position:50% align:center
...you're in love.

00:19:13.486 --> 00:19:15.530 position:50% align:center
You could not be more wrong!

00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:17.490 position:50% align:center
It's gotta be some
kind of a heart disease!

00:19:17.574 --> 00:19:19.701 position:50% align:center
These symptoms never
showed till now!

00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:21.161 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA]
Then, it's your first love.

00:19:21.244 --> 00:19:22.912 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Lady Kaguya?

00:19:22.996 --> 00:19:24.289 position:50% align:center
I'm going to wait outside,

00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.041 position:50% align:center
so why don't you just call me
when you're done here?

00:19:26.124 --> 00:19:27.625 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
You're leaving me?!

00:19:27.709 --> 00:19:30.837 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA] This was my hospital,
too, but after this humiliation,

00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:32.630 position:50% align:center
I don't think
I can ever come back.

00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:34.632 position:50% align:center
What are you talking about?

00:19:34.716 --> 00:19:37.886 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I would like
a proper exam, please.

00:19:42.098 --> 00:19:45.685 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] This is our latest and
greatest medical testing device.

00:19:45.769 --> 00:19:47.312 position:50% align:center
Since it's state-of-the-art
technology,

00:19:47.395 --> 00:19:49.272 position:50% align:center
the fee to use
it is rather steep.

00:19:49.356 --> 00:19:50.565 position:50% align:center
But you'll still proceed?

00:19:50.648 --> 00:19:52.400 position:50% align:center
You can't put a price
on a person's life,

00:19:52.484 --> 00:19:53.693 position:50% align:center
and mine's at stake.

00:19:53.777 --> 00:19:55.779 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 8B]
The measurements are done.

00:19:55.862 --> 00:19:57.072 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA]
And?

00:19:57.155 --> 00:19:58.865 position:50% align:center
She's in possession
of a healthy, happy heart.

00:19:58.948 --> 00:20:00.325 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
I don't believe you!

00:20:00.408 --> 00:20:02.744 position:50% align:center
There had to be at
least a couple holes in it!

00:20:02.827 --> 00:20:04.829 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] You'd be dead
by now if there were.

00:20:04.913 --> 00:20:06.247 position:50% align:center
But I nearly died!

00:20:06.331 --> 00:20:08.291 position:50% align:center
So being in love has the
power to make you topple over

00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:10.126 position:50% align:center
when someone touches your cheek?

00:20:10.210 --> 00:20:12.253 position:50% align:center
I admit, the gesture
was fairly pleasing to me.

00:20:12.337 --> 00:20:14.422 position:50% align:center
But I would literally have to
love the president to death

00:20:14.506 --> 00:20:16.716 position:50% align:center
for me to hit the
floor the way I did!

00:20:16.800 --> 00:20:17.801 position:50% align:center
You wouldn't happen to have

00:20:17.884 --> 00:20:19.469 position:50% align:center
a picture of him on
hand, would you?

00:20:19.552 --> 00:20:22.305 position:50% align:center
Yes, if Hayasaka brings
me my phone, I do.

00:20:22.389 --> 00:20:24.766 position:50% align:center
Stop hiding behind your
hands and get over here!

00:20:24.849 --> 00:20:27.018 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Okay...

00:20:28.937 --> 00:20:31.523 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] You don't have
a normal photo of him?

00:20:31.606 --> 00:20:33.358 position:50% align:center
How strange, yet...

00:20:33.441 --> 00:20:34.859 position:50% align:center
...he seems like a nice kid.

00:20:34.943 --> 00:20:37.737 position:50% align:center
And he's interesting enough
to be a good match for you.

00:20:37.821 --> 00:20:39.322 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Seriously?

00:20:39.406 --> 00:20:41.866 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA] Pardon me for prying,
but do you not wish to date him?

00:20:41.950 --> 00:20:45.161 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA sighs] Our relationship
is a little complicated.

00:20:45.245 --> 00:20:47.706 position:50% align:center
I just find him to be
an ideal human, that's all.

00:20:47.789 --> 00:20:51.042 position:50% align:center
It doesn't mean I have to
date him or anything. Jeez!

00:20:51.126 --> 00:20:52.127 position:50% align:center
Telling me he's a "good match"

00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:54.129 position:50% align:center
doesn't affect me
in the slightest.

00:20:54.212 --> 00:20:56.214 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 8B]
Her pulse is over 200.

00:20:56.297 --> 00:20:57.757 position:50% align:center
It's beating so fast.

00:20:57.841 --> 00:20:58.967 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Stop it!

00:20:59.050 --> 00:21:00.760 position:50% align:center
You shouldn't abuse
your fancy technology

00:21:00.844 --> 00:21:03.138 position:50% align:center
to expose her emotions!
It's not right!

00:21:03.221 --> 00:21:06.141 position:50% align:center
Have you noticed any changes
in her state of mind recently?

00:21:08.893 --> 00:21:10.020 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
The other day,

00:21:10.103 --> 00:21:12.772 position:50% align:center
she came absurdly
close to kissing him.

00:21:12.856 --> 00:21:15.275 position:50% align:center
That incident's been consuming
her thoughts ever since!

00:21:15.358 --> 00:21:16.735 position:50% align:center
Ah, that would explain it, yes.

00:21:16.818 --> 00:21:19.404 position:50% align:center
Shut up, you traitor! That's
totally unrelated to this!

00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:20.989 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
She's in complete denial!

00:21:21.072 --> 00:21:22.991 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] The only emotion I felt
in that situation was terror,

00:21:23.074 --> 00:21:24.659 position:50% align:center
okay?! When he was on top of me,

00:21:24.743 --> 00:21:26.870 position:50% align:center
my mind went blank and
I had no idea what to do!

00:21:26.953 --> 00:21:28.288 position:50% align:center
I was petrified!

00:21:28.371 --> 00:21:31.374 position:50% align:center
I'm not in love with him!
I'm afraid of him!

00:21:39.174 --> 00:21:41.509 position:50% align:center
[TANUMA]
I know exactly how you feel.

00:21:41.593 --> 00:21:44.596 position:50% align:center
There was a time when
I, too, fell in love.

00:21:44.679 --> 00:21:47.807 position:50% align:center
Although, I suppose I never
really outgrew it, I--

00:21:47.891 --> 00:21:50.268 position:50% align:center
I couldn't care less!

00:21:50.352 --> 00:21:51.978 position:50% align:center
He was a quack, not a doctor!

00:21:52.062 --> 00:21:54.272 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
His doctorate begs to disagree.

00:21:54.356 --> 00:21:56.649 position:50% align:center
I'll go get a second
opinion at another hospital!

00:21:56.733 --> 00:21:57.525 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's it!

00:21:57.609 --> 00:21:58.610 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:58.693 --> 00:22:00.779 position:50% align:center
[BOTH grunting]

00:22:00.862 --> 00:22:02.197 position:50% align:center
I am begging you,

00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:05.825 position:50% align:center
do not humiliate me
any more than you have.

00:22:05.909 --> 00:22:10.622 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Results for today's
battle: Hayasaka loses.

00:22:10.705 --> 00:22:12.916 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA wailing]
Kaguya!

00:22:12.999 --> 00:22:14.084 position:50% align:center
Thank goodness you're okay!

00:22:14.167 --> 00:22:16.211 position:50% align:center
Are you sure? Have
you fully recovered?

00:22:16.294 --> 00:22:17.962 position:50% align:center
Yes. I'm just fine.

00:22:18.046 --> 00:22:19.798 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
So, you have a bad heart?

00:22:19.881 --> 00:22:23.051 position:50% align:center
No. I'm told it's
happy and healthy. Yay.

00:22:23.134 --> 00:22:25.095 position:50% align:center
Then what was the
cause of the problem?!

00:22:25.178 --> 00:22:26.221 position:50% align:center
What would make you faint?!

00:22:26.304 --> 00:22:27.055 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
You would.

00:22:27.138 --> 00:22:27.889 position:50% align:center
Tell me!

00:22:27.972 --> 00:22:29.349 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
She can't.

00:22:29.432 --> 00:22:31.935 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Jeez!

00:22:32.018 --> 00:22:33.812 position:50% align:center
It's all your fault, President!

00:22:33.895 --> 00:22:37.524 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Oh, Kaguya. You, <i>tsundere</i> , you.